      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### A Little Chemistry Context\n\n- The **positive E°** means Cu²⁺ is a moderately strong oxidizing agent — copper metal dissolves readily in oxidizing acids (e.g., HNO₃) but **not** in non-oxidizing acids like HCl under standard conditions.\n- This value is central to understanding **copper corrosion**, **electroplating**, and **copper-based batteries**.\n- If you're interested in how **complexation** shifts the *apparent* reduction potential (e.g., Cu²⁺ with ammonia, EDTA, or cyanide), SRD-46 **can** help — the Nernst equation links stability constants to conditional potentials. Just ask! 🔬",
